  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* --- General-mu closed form for b[2] ---\n   b[2] carries Cas2 with coefficient h^2 (this is what makes b[1]=(b[2]-...)/2 carry the\n   (h^2/2)Cas2 that tau1 requires); state-independent part fixed by the vacuum anchor:\n     b[2](mu) = b2vac + h^2 (Cas2[mu] - Cas2[mu_top]),   mu_top = [S+P,S+P,0,0].\n   d[2] (the tau2 constant) is the only coefficient still carrying Cas4; anchor value d2vac. *)\nmutop = {S + P, S + P, 0, 0};\nb2gen[mu_] := b2vac + h^2 (Cas2[mu] - Cas2[mutop]);\nb2gen[{m1, m2, m3, m4}] // Expand",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
