       "data": "{\n\t\"name\": \"WolframKernelMessage\",\n\t\"message\": \"Join::heads: Heads List and Equal at positions 1 and 3 are expected to be the same.\\nTable::iterb: Iterator {j, 0, {2, 1, 1, 0}} does not have appropriate bounds.\\nTable::iterb: Iterator {j, 0, {2, 1, 1, 0}} does not have appropriate bounds.\\nSolve::naqs: Join[{gaudinODE == 0}, {cq[{2, 1, 1, 0}] == 1}, degQ[] == 0] is not a quantified system of equations and inequalities.\\nTable::iterb: Iterator {j, 0, {2, 1, 1, 0}} does not have appropriate bounds.\\nGeneral::stop: Further output of Table::iterb will be suppressed during this calculation.\\nReplaceAll::reps: {Join[{gaudinODE == 0}, {cq[{2, 1, 1, 0}] == 1}, degQ[] == 0]} is neither a list of replacement rules nor a valid dispatch table, and so cannot be used for replacing.\\nJoin::heads: Heads List and Equal at positions 1 and 3 are expected to be the same.\\nSolve::naqs: Join[{gaudinODE == 0}, {cq[1] == 1}, degQ[cq[{2, 1, 1, 0}]] == 0] is not a quantified system of equations and inequalities.\\nReplaceAll::reps: {Join[{gaudinODE == 0}, {cq[1] == 1}, degQ[cq[{2, 1, 1, 0}]] == 0]} is neither a list of replacement rules nor a valid dispatch table, and so cannot be used for replacing.\\nJoin::heads: Heads List and Equal at positions 1 and 3 are expected to be the same.\\nGeneral::stop: Further output of Join::heads will be suppressed during this calculation.\\nSolve::naqs: Join[{gaudinODE == 0}, {cq[1] == 1}, degQ[cq[{2, 1, 1, 0}], cq[1]] == 0] is not a quantified system of equations and inequalities.\\nGeneral::stop: Further output of Solve::naqs will be suppressed during this calculation.\\nReplaceAll::reps: {Join[{gaudinODE == 0}, {cq[1] == 1}, degQ[cq[{2, 1, 1, 0}], cq[1]] == 0]} is neither a list of replacement rules nor a valid dispatch table, and so cannot be used for replacing.\\nGeneral::stop: Further output of ReplaceAll::reps will be suppressed during this calculation.\\nPart::partw: Part 4 of degQ[{2, 1, 1, 0}, 1, 1] does not exist.\",\n\t\"stack\": \"\"\n}",
       "mime": "application/vnd.code.notebook.error"
      }
     ],
     "id": "74817d30-63a5-4762-a2c2-df60cd216b8d"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(* --- (S,P)=(8,8): Gaudin ODE solver over the full [8,8,0,0]x[8,8,0,0] decomposition (45 irreps),\n   theta1=0, theta2=1, per-irrep timing. Each q_k verified to solve the ODE exactly. *)\nirr88 = irreps[8, 8];\ntblG88 = Table[\n   Module[{mu = irr88[[i]], tim, qs, ds, ode, ok, qf},\n     ds = degQ[mu, 8, 8];\n     {tim, qs} = AbsoluteTiming[GaudinSolve[mu, 8, 8]];\n     ode = gaudinODE /. {C2 -> Cas2[mu], C4 -> Cas4[mu], S -> 8, P -> 8} /. thsub;\n     ok = AllTrue[Range[4], (qf = qs[[#]] . u^Range[0, ds[[#]]];\n        Expand[ode /. Q -> Function[x, qf /. u -> x]] === 0) &];\n     {Row[mu, \",\"], dimGL4[mu], Row[ds, \",\"], NumberForm[tim, {6, 4}], ok}],\n   {i, Length[irr88]}];\nPrint[\"# irreps: \", Length[irr88], \"   all solve: \", AllTrue[tblG88, Last],\n   \"   total time (s): \", Total[tblG88[[All, 4]] /. NumberForm[x_, _] :> x]];\nGrid[Prepend[tblG88, {\"mu\", \"dim\", \"deg q_k\", \"time (s)\", \"solves?\"}],\n  Frame -> All, Alignment -> Left,\n  Background -> {None, {RGBColor[.88, .95, .88], {GrayLevel[1], RGBColor[.96, .99, .96]}}}]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
